# Robot Progress
## Climbing:
In the climbing subgroup, discussion continues as we determine whether climbing is even feasible, scoring might provide more points than the climb would allow us to achieve. Realistically, the climbing mechanism will occupy a significant portion of our robot, which could be used to store more balls. While the balls do weigh half a pound, the climb mechanism will be far heavier. The consensus is that we should focus on Level 1 climb, as it would allow us to climb with other robots, earning us extra points. As well as saving space on our robot to maximize our ball-carrying capacities. A significant problem is determining what is strong enough to carry a robot. While we continue to troubleshoot various mechanisms, which include a climber in a box, pulley system, etc. our sights. 
