## Intake:
Our team had decided to do the roller intake. The roller is already prototyped in Onshape. The current intake design is that balls would enter the hopper from the top and be pulled by the belts towards the shooter faster than by gravity. The current consensus on the position of the intake is that it is going to be on the opposite side of the shooter and be the part of the hopper extension.
## Shooter: 
In the shooter subgroup there is a huge debate about which type of shooter would prove to be the most efficient. As shooting is the most important part of the game, it is important for our team to choose the most optimal shooter design. Currently the major unresolved discussions are turret or fixed shooter, single or double barrel, adjustable or fixed hood, and whether shooter should face into the robot or outwards. There are different strong arguments for each option, but the common vision is a double barrel adjustable hood shooter facing inwards. The reasoning is that we have a greater experience with shooters, double barrel would maximize shooting efficiency, adjustable hood would allow shooting from almost anywhere on the field, and finally the inward direction would make shooting while against the hub more feasible because of the lower shooter angle. However, other designs will be prototyped and tested to test our educated assumptions.
